-- Ruble Retreats Versus Dollar as Crude Drops on Europe, China Woe
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n   a n d   L y u b o v   P r o n i n a
-- 2012-09-24T08:13:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/ruble-retreats-versus-dollar-as-crude-drops-on-europe-china-woe.html
The ruble retreated as crude oil,
 Russia ’s main export earner, dropped on concern China’s economic
growth is faltering and  Europe ’s debt crisis won’t be contained.  Russia’s currency dropped 0.7 percent to 31.2400 per dollar
by 11:53 a.m. in Moscow, erasing a 0.7 percent gain on Sept. 21.
The ruble lost 0.2 percent versus the euro to 40.4675 and slid
0.4 percent against the central bank’s target euro-dollar
basket.  Crude for November delivery fell 0.9 percent to $92.08 a
barrel in  New York . Oil and gas contribute about 50 percent of
Russia’s government revenue. Commodities declined on concern
renewed discord between French and German leaders may delay
resolution of the debt crisis that has hurt demand, and as a
report from  China  showed less optimism in the world’s top user.  “The main factor is the reverse of the oil price upward
trend,” Alexei Egorov, an analyst with Moscow-based OAO Nomos
Bank, said by e-mail.  Non-deliverable forwards showed the ruble at 31.6762 per
dollar in three months compared with 31.5000 on Sept. 21.  The extra yield investors demand to own Russia’s dollar
bonds over U.S. Treasuries was unchanged at 201, according to
JPMorgan Chase & Co.’s EMBI Global Index. An index of five-year
government bond yields compiled by the Micex dropped four basis
points to 7.557 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
